step: In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  In a very large bowl  whisk together 12 cups (1.5 kg) of flour  1⁄2 cup (100 g) of sugar  and 2 teaspoons of salt.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Create a well in the center and add 24 eggs.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Stir together vigorously with a large wooden spoon until combined.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Add 1 cup (240 ml) of milk and continue to stir vigorously until combined.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Add 11⁄2 cups (345 g) of the melted butter.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Stir until combined.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Gradually add 14 more cups (3.3 l) of milk to the batter  stirring well after each addition.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Once the batter has loosened a bit  switch from the wooden spoon to a heavy duty whisk.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Whisk vigorously to remove any clumps.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Once the milk is incorporated and there are no more lumps  whisk in 1 cup (240 ml) of water and 2 tablespoons of vanilla.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Repeat steps 1-7 to prepare the second batch of batter.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Pour 1⁄2 cup (120 ml) of batter onto the heated griddle and swirl evenly to coat.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Cook for approximately 2 minutes  until the crepe begins to lightly brown on the bottom.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Flip the crepe and cook for another minute on the other side.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Remove from the pan and set aside to cool.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Repeat 99 more times.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Place the completed crepes in stacks of 10 and store  covered  in the fridge until ready to assemble the cake.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Make the vanilla pastry cream: In a large stock pot set over medium heat  add the egg_yolks  milk  cream  sugar  salt  and cornstarch.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Whisk vigorously to combine.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Whisk constantly until the mixture thickens significantly and bubbles just begin to burst on the surface.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Remove the pot from the heat and add the butter and vanilla.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Repeat to make the other flavors of pastry cream.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Pour the cream onto a baking sheet lined with plastic wrap.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Immediately place in the fridge to cool and set  overnight.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  To assemble the crepe cake  place 1 crepe on a large cutting board or baking sheet (you will need to be able to transfer the cake to and from the freezer).
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Place another crepe directly on top and spread with more pastry cream.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Repeat until you have 25 crepes stacked with the first filling.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Transfer the assembled cake to the freezer to chill for 15 minutes between flavors.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Repeat with each flavor of pastry cream  layering 25 crepes with each flavor filling.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Once assembled  freeze the cake for 30 minutes to set and firm up.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Dust the top with powdered_sugar  then slice and serve.
In the recipe 100 layer giant crepe cake  Sticking a wooden dowel into each slice will help the cake keep its shape.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Lay down about 6 feet (1.8 meters) of tinfoil on a flat surface.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Place place 4 clusters of 2 lasagna_noodles towards the left half of the foil sheet  leaving about a 1⁄2-inch (1 cm) gap in between each cluster.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Fold the right half of foil over the noodles  pressing flat.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  To help you see where the noodles are  run your finger along the edges of the noodles to create a rough outline in the foil.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Fold the top and bottom flaps of foil over  creasing and pressing flat.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Flip the foil sheet onto the table so that it’s now standing  then arrange into a square box  using the 4 groups of noodles as a visual guide.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  In a large pot  melt the butter over medium heat.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Whisk in the flour  cooking until the mixture reaches a light golden color.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Slowly drizzle in the milk and bring to a boil  whisking constantly until smooth.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Mix in salt  pepper  and nutmeg.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Bring to a boil.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Heat oil in a very large pot over high heat.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Once the oil begins to shimmer  add the onions  carrots  and celery and cook until the vegetables have started to sweat but aren’t browning.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Add in the ground_beef and use a wooden spoon or spatula to break up the meat into small pieces.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Add in the tomato_sauce  tomato_paste  chicken_stock  salt  and pepper  stirring to combine evenly and breaking up any last lumps.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Turn down the heat to low  and simmer  covered  for about 2 hours.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  To assemble  line a greased 9x9-inch (23x23-cm) square baking pan with 2 sheets of foil that extend over the sides.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Spread a thin layer of béchamel on the lined baking pan and top with 2 lasagna_noodles.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Spread a thin layer of meat sauce evenly across the noodles  followed by a thin layer of béchamel.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Repeat the layering process  following the order of: 2 noodles  meat sauce  and béchamel.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  After 50 layers  place the foil box over the lasagna  helping it stay upright and stable.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Continue with the layering process until the 99th layer.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Sprinkle Parmesan on top  then cover the whole lasagna with foil.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Bake for about 11⁄2 hours  uncovering the foil halfway  until the top is a deep golden brown.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Cool for at least 2 hours  then carefully lift out the lasagna with the foil sleeves onto a large cutting board.
In the recipe 100 layer lasagna  Peel away the foil walls  then sprinkle the top of the lasagna generously with chives.
In the recipe 11 herbs and spices fried chicken  Beat the eggs into the buttermilk.
In the recipe 11 herbs and spices fried chicken  Add the chicken pieces to the buttermilk mixture and chill for an hour.
In the recipe 11 herbs and spices fried chicken  In a large mixing bowl  mix the flour with all the herbs and spices.
In the recipe 11 herbs and spices fried chicken  Coat the soaked chicken pieces in the herbed flour mixture  shaking off any excess.
In the recipe 11 herbs and spices fried chicken  Fry the chicken in batches for 15 minutes until the chicken is cooked and the skins turn golden brown.
In the recipe 11 herbs and spices fried chicken  Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Make the pesto: In a food processor  combine the basil  garlic  pine_nuts  and olive_oil.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Blend for 30 seconds  or until thick and saucy.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Add the Parmesan and salt and blend for another 30 seconds  or until thoroughly combined.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Cut the top off the loaf of bread.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Use a serrated knife to cut a circle in the center of the bread  then use a large spoon to scoop out the inside.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Try to keep bread in one piece.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Use a rolling pin to roll the excess bread into one flat piece of bread.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Spread melted butter on both side of the rolled out bread and bake for 10 minutes  or until golden brown.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Remove the toasted bread from the oven.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Assemble the sandwich: Place bread bowl in an oven-safe pan.

In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Spread pesto on the bottom of the inside of the bread bowl  then layer in half of the mozzarella slices  4 slices of tomatoes  5 slices of turkey  and 4 chopped slices of bacon.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Top with the toasted bread and brush with pesto.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Add the remaining bacon  turkey  tomato  and cheese.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Finally  spread pesto on the bottom lid of the bread and over the cheese.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Place the lid of bread on top of it and then press down with a heavy oven-safe pan.
In the recipe 12 layer turkey pesto panini bread bowl  Bake for 20 minutes  or until golden brown.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  In a large heatproof bowl  pour the hot heavy_cream over the semisweet chocolate_chips.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Let stand for 30 seconds  then whisk together for 1 minute  or until thick and smooth.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Place 1 cup (85 g) of marshmallow fluff in a medium heatproof bowl and place the remaining fluff into a separate medium heatproof bowl.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Add a tablespoon of milk to the bowl with 1 cup (85 g) of fluff and the remaining 2 tablespoons milk to the bowl with the remaining fluff.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Microwave each bowl of fluff for 15 seconds.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Remove the bowls from the microwave and use a fork to stir the milk into the fluff until it is thick and smooth.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Cover the bowl with less fluff and store in the fridge – it will be used later for decoration.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Line a 5x8-inch (13x20cm) loaf pan with parchment paper and place a row of graham_crackers on the bottom of the pan.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Pour a thin layer of the marshmallow fluff over the graham_crackers and use a spoon or spatula to spread the mixture evenly.

In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Place another row of graham_crackers on top of the fluff  then pour a thin layer of the chocolate ganache over the crackers and use a spoon or spatula to spread an even layer.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Repeat three more times.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Cover and chill in the fridge overnight.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Use the parchment to lift the cake out of the loaf pan.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Microwave the leftover marshmallow fluff mixture for 15 seconds  then use a spatula to spread the fluff over the cake in an even layer.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Optional: use a small kitchen torch to gently toast the marshmallow topping.
In the recipe 16 layer no bake smores cake  Sprinkle crumbled graham cracker and chocolate chunks over the top of the cake.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Lightly flour a clean work surface.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Flour a rolling pin and roll out each puff_pastry sheet to flatten the seams.

In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Make a diagonal cut across the 2 bottom sheets of puff_pastry from the lower right corner to the midpoint on the left side of the lower left sheet.

In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Make another diagonal cut across the 2 top sheets of puff_pastry from the upper right corner to the midpoint on the left side of the upper left sheet.

In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Holding the bottom pieces together  rotate clockwise 180 ̊ and up  so that the left side of the bottom strip meets the left side of the lower middle strip.

In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Holding the top pieces together  rotate counterclockwise 180 ̊ and down  so that the left side of the top strip meets the left side of the up middle strip.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Seal the seams by brushing a bit of egg wash where the pieces of pastry meet  overlapping the pieces slightly  and pressing together.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Arrange the cheese slices in a single layer across the lower portion of the triangle.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Top with a single layer of ham slices.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Roll up the puff_pastry from the base of the triangle to the top point.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Place the croissant on the prepared baking sheet and cover with aluminum foil.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Bake for 45 minutes
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Remove the croissant from the oven  take off the foil  and brush the croissant with egg wash.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Bake for another 1 hour and 15 minutes  until the croissant is golden brown.
In the recipe 18 inches long ham and cheese swirl croissant  Let cool for 20 minutes  then slice and serve.
In the recipe 2 1 2 hour tomato sauce  In a pot over medium heat  add the olive_oil and garlic.
In the recipe 2 1 2 hour tomato sauce  Cook for about 2 minutes or until fragrant  but not browned.
In the recipe 2 1 2 hour tomato sauce  Add the tomatoes with their juice  and crush with the back of a spoon.
In the recipe 2 1 2 hour tomato sauce  Add the onion and salt  and stir occasionally.
In the recipe 2 1 2 hour tomato sauce  Bring to a boil  then reduce to a simmer for an hour.
In the recipe 2 1 2 hour tomato sauce  Discard the garlic and onion  then puree to the desired consistency with a food mill or immersion blender.
In the recipe 2 1 2 hour tomato sauce  Transfer the sauce back to a pot and add the bay_leaf  dried_oregano  and dried_basil.
In the recipe 2 1 2 hour tomato sauce  Bring to a simmer for about 90 minutes or until the desired thickness.
In the recipe 2 1 2 hour tomato sauce  Discard the bay_leaf  add the fresh_basil and  to taste  salt  pepper  and sugar.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  Thinly slice the apple and place in a medium bowl with the water and lemon juice to prevent browning.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  Cut the cheese slices into thirds.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  Cut the bread slices into quarters.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  To quickly cut the tomatoes and grapes  place between the bottoms of two plates and slice horizontally.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  Lay out 4 slices of turkey_breast.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  Place a piece of cheese and an apple slice on the upper half of each one  then wrap the turkey around them  tucking the ends underneath.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  Serve with half the grapes  half the cherry tomatoes  and crackers.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  Slice the 4 remaining turkey slices into quarters.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  Layer the bread  turkey  cheese  and remaining cherry tomatoes on the skewers.
In the recipe 2 easy make ahead school lunches  Serve with remaining grapes and apple slices.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate cake  Place the chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl and melt completely  about 1 minute.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate cake  Separate the egg yolks and egg whites.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate cake  Using a hand mixer  whisk the whites until soft peaks form.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate cake  Add the yolks  one by one  into the bowl of chocolate  whisking to combine.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate cake  Using a rubber spatula  gently fold 1⁄3 of the whipped egg whites into the yolk and chocolate mixture.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate cake  Pour the batter in a greased 6-inch (15 cm) cake mold.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate cake  Bake for 30 minutes.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate cake  Once the cake is cool to the touch  gently invert it onto a plate.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate cake  Optional: Sprinkle with powdered_sugar  slice and serve top with ice cream.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate souffle  Separate the egg yolks from the egg whites and place into two bowls.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate souffle  Mix the chocolate_hazelnut_spread into the bowl with the egg yolks.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate souffle  In the second bowl  whisk 2 egg whites until stiff peaks form.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate souffle  Fold 1⁄3 of the whipped egg whites into the chocolate/egg yolk mixture until fully incorporated.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate souffle  Add the remaining egg whites to the mixture and fold gently  but thoroughly  until the mixture is smooth.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate souffle  Pour the mixture into a greased ramekin.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate souffle  Clean the rims so the soufflé rises evenly  and bake for 15-17 minutes.
In the recipe 2 ingredient chocolate souffle  Serve immediately.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough bagels  Transfer the dough ball to a lightly floured work surface and use your hands to begin flattening and shaping the rough into a roughly 8-inch (20 cm) disk.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough bagels  Using a bench scraper or knife  cut the dough into 4 equal pieces.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough bagels  One at a time  roll each piece of dough into a log roughly 8 inches (20 cm) long.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough bagels  Shape the log into a ring and transfer to a parchment paper-lined baking sheet.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough bagels  Brush the tops of the bagels with egg wash and sprinkle generously with everything seasoning.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough bagels  Bake for 20-25 minutes  until the bagels are golden brown.

In the recipe 2 ingredient dough garlic knots  Transfer the dough ball to a lightly floured work surface and use your hands to begin flattening and shaping the rough into a roughly 8-inch (20 cm) disk.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough garlic knots  Using a bench scraper or knife  cut the dough into 8 equal pieces.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough garlic knots  One at a time  roll each piece out into a roughly 12 inch (30 cm) log and set aside.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough garlic knots  Transfer the dough logs to a parchment paper-lined baking sheet and shape individual knots.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough garlic knots  Repeat with remaining logs.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough garlic knots  In a small bowl  mix together the olive_oil  garlic  parsley  and salt.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough garlic knots  Brush each knot with garlic oil mixture.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough garlic knots  Bake for 20 minutes  until the garlic knots have begun to turn golden brown.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pizza  In a large bowl  mix the self-rising flour and Greek yogurt until it comes together to form a ball.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pizza  Transfer the dough ball to a lightly floured work surface and use your hands to begin flattening and shaping the rough into about a 12-inch (30 cm) round.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pizza  Carefully transfer the dough to a lightly floured baking sheet.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pizza  Spread the sauce evenly across the dough  sprinkle on the cheese  and top with pepperonis.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pizza  Bake for 20 minutes  until the cheese has melted and the crust has turned golden-brown.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pizza  Slice and serve.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pretzels  Transfer the dough ball to a lightly floured work surface and use your hands to begin flattening and shaping the rough into a roughly 8-inch (20 cm) disk.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pretzels  Using a bench scraper or knife  cut the dough into 8 equal pieces.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pretzels  One at a time  roll each piece out into a roughly 14-inch (35 cm) log.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pretzels  Transfer the logs to a parchment paper-lined baking sheet and shape into individual pretzels.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pretzels  Brush the pretzels with egg wash and sprinkle with salt.
In the recipe 2 ingredient dough pretzels  Bake for 20 minutes  until the pretzels are a deep golden brown.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pasta  Add the mozzarella to a bowl and microwave for 1-2 minutes  until melted.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pasta  Allow the mozzarella to cool for 30 seconds.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pasta  With a spatula  gently fold the egg_yolk into the cheese.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pasta  Turn the mixture out onto a parchment paper-lined baking sheet.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pasta  Place another piece of parchment paper on top of the dough and press down with your hand until thin.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pasta  Remove the top piece of parchment and cut the dough into thin strips.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pasta  Place the “pasta” on a rack and refrigerate for four hours or overnight.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pasta  Place the “pasta” in boiling water for one minute.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pasta  Serve with your favorite sauce and toppings.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pumpkin bread  Mix the spice_cake_mix and pureed pumpkin.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pumpkin bread  Spread into a greased loaf pan.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pumpkin bread  Bake at 350°F (177°C) for 55-60 min.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pumpkin bread  Cool completely.
In the recipe 2 ingredient pumpkin bread  Frost to your liking!
In the recipe 2 ingredient soda pop cakes  Mix one box of cake_mix with one 12 oz (255 ml) can of soda.
In the recipe 2 ingredient soda pop cakes  Pour into a greased glass baking dish.
In the recipe 2 ingredient soda pop cakes  Bake at 350°F (180°C) for 30-40 minutes (depends on the cake_mix/soda combination).
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Whisk the flour  baking_powder  salt  and cinnamon together in a medium bowl.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  In a separate large bowl  beat the eggs and sugar together with an electric mixer until light  fluffy  and nearly doubled in size  6-8 minutes.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Using a spatula  gently fold in the flour mixture until just combined (some streaks of flour are okay).
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Combine the milk and vanilla_extract in a liquid measuring cup or small bowl  then gently fold into the batter  mixing just to blend.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Divide the batter between the pans.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Bake until the cakes are golden brown around the edges and spring back slightly when pressed in the center  about 20-25 minutes.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  While the cakes are baking  combine the evaporated_milk  coconut_milk and condensed_milk in a liquid measuring cup or small bowl and whisk to blend.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Once the cakes are done  immediately remove the cakes from the pans and invert them onto a wire rack or baking sheet.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Then  poke the cakes all over with a fork.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Return the cakes to the pans.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Drizzle the condensed_milk mixture over the cakes  letting it soak in.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Let sit for 15 minutes.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  In a medium bowl  whip the heavy cream and powdered_sugar with an electric hand mixer until stiff peaks form.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Spread a layer of the whipped cream over the cake.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Place the other cake on top and spread with the remaining whipped cream.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Decorate with berries  if desired.
In the recipe 2 layer tres leches cake  Slice and serve.
In the recipe 2 minute sweet potato chips  Working in batches  place the sliced sweet_potatoes on a piece of parchment paper and sprinkle with salt.
In the recipe 2 minute sweet potato chips  Microwave for 2 minutes and 30 seconds  flipping halfway  until the chips begin to brown.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Place the ramen_noodles in a large bowl (discard the seasoning packets or save for another use) and pour the boiling_water over them.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Let sit for 6 minutes  stirring every now and then to break up the noodle blocks.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Drain and rinse under cold water.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  In a small bowl  combine the garlic  cornstarch  sesame_oil  lime_juice  and soy_sauce.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Stir well  then set aside.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Place the broccoli in a large  microwave-safe bowl and microwave for 11⁄2 minutes  until soft.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Set aside.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Heat 1 teaspoon of olive_oil in a large  nonstick pan over high heat.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Add the steak to the pan and toss with 2 tablespoons of the reserved sauce.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Cook until browned  about 2 minutes.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Remove from the pan and set aside.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Heat another teaspoon of olive_oil in the pan  then add the onion.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Cook  stirring often  until browned  about 4 minutes.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Add the broccoli and cook until lightly browned  about 2 minutes.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Remove from the pan and set aside.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Add the remaining teaspoon of olive_oil to the pan  then add the noodles and the remaining sauce.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Cook  stirring constantly  until the noodles soak up the sauce.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Return the cooked vegetables and steak to the pan and stir to distribute.
In the recipe 20 minute beef and broccoli noodle stir fry  Transfer the noodles to a serving dish and garnish with green onions  cilantro  and sesame_seeds  if using.
In the recipe 20 minute one pan pizza  In a large nonstick pan  combine the warm_water  olive_oil  flour  sugar  yeast  and salt.
In the recipe 20 minute one pan pizza  Use a spatula to stir the ingredients  then smooth the dough to the edges of the pan.
In the recipe 20 minute one pan pizza  Spread the marinara_sauce over the dough  all the way to the edges.
In the recipe 20 minute one pan pizza  Sprinkle the mozzarella evenly over the sauce  then top with the pepperoni.
In the recipe 20 minute one pan pizza  Place over medium heat  cover  and cook for 10 minutes with the vent covered.
In the recipe 20 minute one pan pizza  Uncover the vent and cook for 5 more minutes  until the edges are crispy.
In the recipe 20 minute one pan pizza  Slide the pizza out of the pan onto a cutting board and let cool for 5 minutes.
In the recipe 20 minute one pan pizza  Sprinkle with basil  then slice and serve.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  To clean mussels  scrub them with a stiff brush under cold running water to remove any grit.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Discard any mussels with cracked or broken shells  or that do not close.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  In a large lidded pot over medium-high heat  stir butter until melted.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Add the onion and cook  stirring frequently  until it has softened and started to brown  6-8 minutes.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Add the garlic and cook for 30 seconds  stirring constantly.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Add the red_pepper_flakes and season with salt.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Stir to combine.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Add the mussels and stir until completely coated.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Add the white_wine and stir.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Put the lid on the pot and cook until the mussels have opened  3-5 minutes.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Discard any shells that don’t open after 5 minutes.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Add the parsley and stir.
In the recipe 25 minute mussels in white wine  Serve with bread.
In the recipe 3 cheese garlic bread  In a bowl  combine all of the ingredients except the baguette  and mix until smooth.
In the recipe 3 cheese garlic bread  Slice the baguette in half lengthwise  then spread the butter mixture evenly on both sides of the baguette.
In the recipe 3 cheese garlic bread  Place on a tray lined with parchment paper and bake for about 15 minutes  until cheese is bubbly and starting to brown on the edges.
In the recipe 3 cheese garlic bread  Slice  cool  then serve.
In the recipe 3 ingredient banana oat smoothie  Add rolled_oats to a blender and blend until the oats are the size of a fine crumb.
In the recipe 3 ingredient banana oat smoothie  Add the banana and milk and blend well.
In the recipe 3 ingredient banana oat smoothie  Pour in a glass  and enjoy!
In the recipe 3 ingredient brazilian truffles  Put a pot on a medium low heat and melt the butter with the condensed milk.
In the recipe 3 ingredient brazilian truffles  Stir in the cocoa_powder and continue to stir for 10-15 minutes until the mixture begins to pull away from the edge of the pot.
In the recipe 3 ingredient brazilian truffles  It’s done when you run the spoon through the centre of the mixture and it takes a few seconds to combine again.
In the recipe 3 ingredient brazilian truffles  Spread the mixture onto a buttered plate and refrigerate for 2 hours.

In the recipe 3 ingredient brazilian truffles  When set  roll the mixture into small balls and coat them in the chocolate sprinkles (you may need to apply a small amount of butter to your hands to help them from sticking).
In the recipe 3 ingredient breakfast cookies  In a large mixing bowl combine the oats and banana and mash banana and mix until well incorporated.
In the recipe 3 ingredient breakfast cookies  Add additional ingredients should you desire.
In the recipe 3 ingredient breakfast cookies  Bake for 12 minutes.
In the recipe 3 ingredient cajun bbq ribs  Rub the Cajun seasoning evenly over the top and bottom of the ribs.
In the recipe 3 ingredient cajun bbq ribs  Bake for 2 hours  until ribs are tender.
In the recipe 3 ingredient cajun bbq ribs  Brush the BBQ sauce evenly over the top and the sides.
In the recipe 3 ingredient cajun bbq ribs  Bake for an additional 15 minutes  until the sauce is bubbly and caramelized.

In the recipe bacon wrapped mashed potato stuffed meatloaf  Line a bundt pan with slices of bacon and use a pastry brush to spread a layer of glaze on the inside of the bacon.

In the recipe bacon wrapped mashed potato stuffed meatloaf  Add 2⁄3 of the meat to the bottom of the bundt pan and spread up the sides and up the middle of the pan making a “bowl” for the mashed potatoes.
In the recipe bacon wrapped mashed potato stuffed meatloaf  Add the mashed potatoes into the “bowl” and smooth out.

In the recipe bacon wrapped mashed potato stuffed meatloaf  Top the mashed potatoes with the remaining meat  smooth out  coat the top with the raw meat glaze  and fold the slices of bacon over the top of the meat.

In the recipe bacon wrapped mashed potato stuffed meatloaf  Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour  remove the foil after 30 minutes and carefully drain some of the fat before putting it back into the oven.
In the recipe bacon wrapped mashed potato stuffed meatloaf  Place a cooling rack on top of the bundt pan and flip over onto a baking sheet.
In the recipe bacon wrapped mashed potato stuffed meatloaf  Remove the bundt pan and coat the meatloaf with the reserved glaze.
In the recipe bacon wrapped mashed potato stuffed meatloaf  Broil on high for 3-5 minutes or until the glaze has caramelized.
In the recipe bacon wrapped mozzarella sticks  Freeze the string cheese (for at least a few hours)

In the recipe bacon wrapped mozzarella sticks  Once folded wrap/roll the cheese in a second slice of bacon.

In the recipe bacon wrapped parmesan garlic knots  Grease the large bowl with the remaining tablespoon of olive_oil.

In the recipe bacon wrapped parmesan garlic knots  Garnish with chopped parsley.
In the recipe bacon wrapped parmesan garlic knots  Serve with marinara_sauce alongside.

In the recipe bacon wrapped prime rib  Season all over with salt and freshly ground pepper.

In the recipe beef and cheese tortellini bake  Layer as follows: tortellini  cheese  basil  sauce  tortellini  cheese  basil  sauce  and cheese.
In the recipe beef and cheese tortellini bake  Bake for 15-20 minutes  or until cheese is melted and bubbling.
In the recipe beef and cheese tortellini bake  Cool for several minutes and serve.
In the recipe beef bean burritos  Add ground_beef to a large skillet over high heat and sprinkle with taco_seasoning.
In the recipe beef bean burritos  Cook  breaking up the meat  until browned.

In the recipe beef bean burritos  Assemble the burritos by microwaving the flour tortilla for 20 seconds  and begin to layer burrito starting with refried beans  followed by the cooked beef and cheese.
In the recipe beef bean burritos  Fold in the left and right sides of the tortilla and roll it up from the bottom  tucking the bottom edge under the filling.
In the recipe beef bean burritos  Wrap in parchment paper and label.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Heat half of the butter in large pot or Dutch oven.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Add the beef  in batches  browning all sides of the meat.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Transfer the beef to a bowl and set aside.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Clean the pot.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  In the same pan  heat remaining butter  then add in the onion  celery  and carrot.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Cook until softened.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Add in the beer.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  With a wooden spatula  scrape off the browned bits on the bottom of the pan to further flavour the stock.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Add in the seared beef  tomato purée  bay_leaves  juniper_berries  and 2 teaspoons each of salt and pepper.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Bring the stew to a boil  cover  and simmer for 2-4 hours  until the beef becomes tender.
In the recipe beef beer goulash  Serve topped with parsley.

In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  In a medium bowl  combine the bread crumbs  pecorino Romano  1⁄2 cup (20 g) chopped basil  provolone  parsley  5 minced cloves of garlic  salt  pepper  and the olive_oil.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Stir and set aside.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Lay the flank_steak on a cutting board.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Season both sides with salt and pepper.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Cover the the meat with a sheet of parchment paper.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Using a meat mallet or rolling pin  pound the steak until it’s 1⁄4 inch (6 mm) thick.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Remove the parchment and sprinkle the bread crumb mixture evenly over the steak.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Starting from the bottom  roll the meat into a log.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Using butcher’s twine  tie up the roll so it holds its shape while cooking.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Season with salt and pepper.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Heat the canola_oil in a large Dutch oven over high heat.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  When the oil is shimmering  add the steak roll and  without moving it  cook until a dark brown crust forms on one side  about 3 minutes.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Turn the roll and repeat until all sides and the ends have been seared.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Remove the roll from the pan and set aside.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Add the butter  carrot  onion  celery  remaining 3 cloves of garlic  salt  and pepper to the pan and cook until caramelized  about 5 minutes.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Add the white wine and stir to loosen any brown bits from the bottom of the pot.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Add the tomatoes  bay_leaves  oregano  and red_pepper_flakes.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Stir to combine.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Return the beef roll to the pot.

In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Cover and bake for 1 hour  flipping the roll halfway through (if the sauce is drying up too much  add more crushed_tomatoes or water)  until the beef is tender.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Slice the braciole and arrange on a serving platter with the sauce.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Serve the braciole with orecchiette or polenta.
In the recipe beef braciole stuffed italian beef roll  Garnish with grated pecorino Romano and fresh_basil.
In the recipe beef broccoli cauliflower fried rice  In a large saucepan over medium-high heat  cook the steak until no pink is showing.
In the recipe beef broccoli cauliflower fried rice  Add the broccoli  salt  pepper  soy_sauce  and brown_sugar.
In the recipe beef broccoli cauliflower fried rice  Cook for 4-5 minutes until most of the liquid has reduced.
In the recipe beef broccoli cauliflower fried rice  Add the cauliflower rice  then cook for about 3-4 more minutes.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  In a 2-cup (480 ml) liquid measuring cup  combine the water  cornstarch  soy_sauce  garlic  brown_sugar  and white_pepper.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  In a medium bowl  season the steak strips with salt.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  Pour half of the sauce over the meat and set the rest aside for later.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  Mix the sauce with the steak  cover with plastic wrap  and marinate in the refrigerator for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  In the same wok  add 1 tablespoon of cooking_oil and the marinated beef.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  Cook the beef for 3-4 minutes  then flip and cook for another 2 minutes  or until slightly crispy.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  Remove from the wok and set aside.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  In the same wok  heat the remaining tablespoon of oil and add onion and broccoli.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  Season with salt  then stir and cook for 3-4 minutes  or until the onions are translucent.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  Return the steak to the wok  followed by the crispy noodles and sesame_oil.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  Mix well and pour in the reserved sauce.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  Toss gently and cook for another 2-3 minutes  or until everything is well-combined.
In the recipe beef broccoli chow mein  Garnish with sliced scallions.
In the recipe beef broccoli fried rice  Pour soy_sauce  sesame_oil  garlic  brown_sugar  water  and cornstarch over the strips of beef.
In the recipe beef broccoli fried rice  Mix well  and marinate in the refrigerator for at least an hour.
In the recipe beef broccoli fried rice  In a wok or deep skillet  cook the beef in the marinade thoroughly and set aside.
In the recipe beef broccoli fried rice  In the same pan  heat up the oil and cook onions  garlic  and broccoli until onions are translucent.
In the recipe beef broccoli fried rice  Push all of the cooked vegetables to the side of the pan.
In the recipe beef broccoli fried rice  Beat the eggs and pour into the cleared half of the pan.
In the recipe beef broccoli fried rice  Scramble the eggs and mix with the rest of the vegetables.
In the recipe beef broccoli fried rice  Add rice  soy_sauce  sesame_oil  pepper  and cooked beef.
In the recipe beef broccoli fried rice  Mix well and let the rice cook until slightly crispy.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Pour the washed rice into a large pot and add 3 cups (720 ml) of fresh water.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Let soak for 30 minutes.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Place the rice on the stove over medium-high heat and bring to a boil.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Cover  reduce the heat to low  and simmer for 12 minutes  or until all of the water is absorbed by the rice.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Turn off the heat and let the rice rest with the lid on for 10 minutes  then fluff the rice and set aside until ready to use.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Make the stir fry sauce: In a liquid measuring cup or medium bowl  combine the soy_sauce  honey  ginger  and garlic.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Whisk to combine.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Make the filling: Heat the vegetable_oil in a medium pan over medium heat.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Add the beef  salt  and pepper and cook until the meat is browned and cooked all the way through  3-4 minutes.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Remove the beef from the pan.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Add the onion and broccoli to the same pan.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Cook for 2-3 minutes  until slightly tender.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Add the stir fry sauce.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Combine the cornstarch and water in a small bowl and stir until cornstarch dissolves.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Pour into the pan.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Cook for 2-3 minutes more  or until the sauce is thick and the broccoli is tender.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Return the beef to the pan  add the sesame_seeds  and stir until thoroughly combined.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Line a 5-inch (13 cm) diameter bowl with plastic wrap.

In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Scoop two tablespoons of rice into the bowl and use the back of a spoon (or your fingers) to flatten in an even layer against the inside of the bowl.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Add a 1⁄2 tablespoon of filling and top it off with a little more rice.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Use the plastic wrap to mold the rice around the filling.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Unwrap and use your hands to shape the rice into a triangle.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  In a medium pan  heat the vegetable_oil over medium-high heat.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Add 2-3 rice triangles to the pan and fry on each side for 1-2 minutes  or until the rice is crispy and starting to turn golden brown.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Brush soy_sauce on all sides of the triangles and fry each side for another 1-2 minutes  or until dark golden brown.
In the recipe beef broccoli stuffed rice triangles  Sprinkle the rice triangles with scallions  then serve.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Sprinkle the salt and pepper evenly over both sides of the beef.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Cut the beef into 1-inch (2 1⁄2 cm) strips.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Dredge the beef in the egg  then roll it in the bread crumbs  pressing as many bread crumbs into the beef as possible.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Pan fry the breaded beef strips until golden brown on both sides.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Remove and drain.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Cut the baguette into 4-inch (10 cm) long pieces.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Hollow out the insides of each baguette piece.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Spread the beans evenly inside the baguette pieces (optional).
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Place one mozzarella slice on top of the other with a 1-inch (2 1⁄2 cm) overlap.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Put the breaded beef strip in the middle  then top with a slice of avocado.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Wrap the cheese tightly around the beef and avocado  then push it inside the hollowed out baguette piece.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Slice the stuffed baguette piece into 1-inch (2 1⁄2 cm) slices.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Place the baguette slices side by side on a baking sheet lined with foil.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Mix the butter with the garlic  parsley  and parmesan.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Brush the garlic butter mixture evenly on top of the baguette slices.
In the recipe beef cutlet stuffed garlic bread  Wrap the foil around the bread  then bake for 20 minutes  until cheese is melted and the garlic on top is golden brown.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  In a re-sealable freezer bag  add beef  garlic  coriander  cumin  paprika  white vinegar  and olive_oil.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  Seal the bag and distribute seasonings.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  Allow to marinate in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  In a food processor  add garlic_cloves and pulse until the garlic becomes finely minced.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  Add salt and pulse until well incorporated.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  Scrape down the sides of the bowl if you see the garlic building up on the sides.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  Turn on the food processor and keep it on.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  In a thin stream pour 1⁄2 cup (59 ml) of oil followed by 1⁄2 tsp of lemon_juice.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  Keep alternating until you have used all of the oil and lemon_juice.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  The garlic sauce should become light  fluffy and creamy.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  Store garlic sauce in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 1 week!
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  To assemble the kebabs  spray skewers with non-stick cooking spray and alternate threading beef  onions and bell_peppers onto the skewer.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  Cook 5-7 minutes on each side.
In the recipe beef kebab with garlic sauce  Serve kebabs with garlic sauce  salad  rice  hummus  and pita bread.
In the recipe beef ragu  Add a few ladlefuls of ragu  the pasta  and a splash of pasta water to a large pot  gently stir to coat the pasta in the ragu.
In the recipe beef ragu  Add a handful of cheese and stir to melt into the sauce.
In the recipe beef ragu  Garnish with more cheese and fresh_parsley before serving.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Add salt and pepper to the flour and use it to coat the diced beef.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Brown off beef in a deep ovenproof pan with olive_oil.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Remove from pan.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Add more oil and fry the onions until translucent.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Add the carrots and celery and fry for another 3-5 minutes.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Add the garlic and fry for 2 minutes together with the beef.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Add in the tomato_puree and rosemary and fry for a further 2-3 minutes.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Add the chopped_tomato and cook for 2 minutes.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Add the red_wine and allow to reduce slightly.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Add the beef_stock and allow to reduce for 10 minutes.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Cover the pot with a lid and cook for 2 hours.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Remove and cover the top of the stew with thinly-chopped peeled potatoes  arranged so they are overlapping slightly.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Cover with melted butter  salt  pepper  and thyme and cook for a further 45 minutes at 200°C (400 ̊F) with the lid off.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Remove from oven once potatoes are cooked and cover with the grated gruyere.
In the recipe beef stew gratin  Grill on high for 5-10 minutes until cheese is bubbling.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  In a medium bowl  season the beef with salt and pepper and toss to coat.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Add 1⁄4 cup (30 g) of flour  and toss the beef cubes until they are fully coated.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Place about half of the beef cubes in the pan.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Sear the beef on one side until it develops a deep brown crust  3-5 minutes.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Then flip and sear on the other side for 3-5 minutes.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Then  stir the beef until evenly browned on all sides.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Melt the butter in the leftover meat drippings.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Add the onion  season with salt and pepper  and cook until the onions are soft and slightly golden  about 5 minutes.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Add the sliced mushrooms and cook until deeply browned and tender  about 10 minutes.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Add the cognac and scrape the brown bits  releasing them from the bottom of the pan.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Cook and stir until the cognac is fully incorporated  about 2 minutes.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Sprinkle the remaining 1⁄4 cup (30 g) flour into the pan and stir to coat the the caramelized veggies.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Add the beef_broth and stir it into the flour and vegetables.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Bring the liquid to a boil  then reduce to low heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  The sauce should be thick enough to coat the back of a spoon.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Put two scoops of hot gravy into a bowl with the sour_cream.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Mix the two together to slightly warm  or temper  the sour_cream.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Then add the sour_cream mixture to the rest of the gravy and stir it in until fully combined.
In the recipe beef stroganoff  Sprinkle the stroganoff with chopped parsley and serve with buttered egg noodles  rice  or potatoes.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Half the potatoes and scoop out the insides  keeping the scooped out potato for later.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Cut the steak into thin strips and sear in a hot pan.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Remove the steak.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Melt the butter in the pan  then add the onions and garlic.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Season with salt.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Cook the onions and garlic until translucent  then add the mushrooms.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  When the mushrooms are soft  stir in the mustard  paprika  and leftover potato.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Stir in the beef_stock  then simmer until mostly reduced.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Add the soured cream  then add the seared beef back in as well.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Season with salt and pepper and remove from the heat immediately.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Stuff the potato skins with the stroganoff mixture.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Bake for 8-10 minutes.
In the recipe beef stroganoff potatoes  Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  In a food processor  place mushrooms  garlic  salt  pepper  and thyme and blend into a fine paste (about 30-60 seconds).
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Transfer to a medium-sized frying pan  being sure to spread it evenly across the bottom of the pan.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Cook the mushrooms over medium-low heat while stirring frequently.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  At this point  remove the mushroom mixture from the heat and set it aside.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Liberally season the outside of the tenderloin pieces with salt and pepper.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Once the oil has begun to smoke  quickly sear the tenderloin pieces on both sides (45-60 seconds per-side).
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Once seared  transfer the meat to a plate or cutting board to rest.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Using a basting brush  generously paint the mustard over the resting pieces of beef  making sure to coat both sides.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  To assemble the Wellingtons  lay out a piece of puff_pastry on a lightly floured surface.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Place a piece of ham in the center of the pasty.

In the recipe beef wellington for two  Next  layer about 1 tablespoon of the mushroom mixture on the center of the ham using the back of a spoon to flatten the paste to about the size of the tenderloin pieces.

In the recipe beef wellington for two  Place one of the mustard-coated beef fillet on top of the mushroom mixture  then top the piece of beef with another spoonful of the mushroom mixture  making sure to pat it down flat across the top of the meat.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Layer with another piece of ham and close the the Wellington by folding the puff_pastry over the center of the meat.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Using your hands  carefully seal the edges of the pastry then transfer SEAM-SIDE DOWN to a baking tray lined with parchment paper.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Lightly brush the outside of each Wellington with egg_wash.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Using the back of a paring knife  lightly score the tops of the pasty in a checkered pattern  being careful not to pierce the pastry.
In the recipe beef wellington for two  Bake the Wellingtons in a 400 ̊F (200 ̊C) oven until the pastry is fully cooked and golden brown (about 20 minutes).
In the recipe beer batter apple rings  In a bowl  whisk together flour  cinnamon  and Redd’s Apple Ale until smooth.
In the recipe beer batter apple rings  Slice off the top and bottom of the apples  and slice each apple into 1⁄2-inch (1 cm) thick rounds.
In the recipe beer batter apple rings  With a teaspoon or large piping tip  cut out a circle in the center of the apple ring to make it look like a donut.
In the recipe beer batter apple rings  Dip the apple slices in the batter.
In the recipe beer batter apple rings  Fry them two to three at a time.
In the recipe beer batter apple rings  Flip each apple slice once during frying and fry until both sides are golden brown.
In the recipe beer batter apple rings  Carefully remove from the oil and place onto paper towels or a drying rack.
In the recipe beer batter apple rings  Cool  then sprinkle with powdered_sugar.
In the recipe beer battered crispy fried chicken  Pour the crisps into a ziplock bag and smash into pieces using a rolling pin.
In the recipe beer battered crispy fried chicken  Pour into a bowl and set aside.
In the recipe beer battered crispy fried chicken  Mix all the beer batter ingredients in a bowl until combined  careful not to overmix.
In the recipe beer battered crispy fried chicken  Cut the chicken into strips and coat well in the batter  then the crisp coating.
In the recipe beer battered crispy fried chicken  Fry for about 2-3 minutes on each side  or until chicken is golden brown and cooked through.
In the recipe beer battered crispy fried chicken  Transfer to some paper towel to soak up some of the excess oil.
In the recipe beer battered crispy fried chicken  Serve with chips  your favourite sauces and leftover beer.
In the recipe beer battered onion rings by martha stewart  Peel and cut onions crosswise into 1⁄2 (1 1⁄3 cm) inch slices.
In the recipe beer battered onion rings by martha stewart  Separate into rings and place in a large bowl with ice_water while you prepare the batter.
In the recipe beer battered onion rings by martha stewart  In a medium mixing bowl  whisk together 1 cup flour (125 g)  salt  white_pepper  and baking_powder.
In the recipe beer battered onion rings by martha stewart  Whisk in beer and 2 tablespoons of ice_water until just combined.
In the recipe beer battered onion rings by martha stewart  In a separate bowl  add the remaining 1 cup (125 g) of flour.
In the recipe beer battered onion rings by martha stewart  Coat the rings first in the flour then in the batter  allowing any excess to drip off.
In the recipe beer battered onion rings by martha stewart  Working in batches  transfer battered rings to hot oil to cook for 2 to 3 minutes  or until golden brown.
In the recipe beer battered onion rings by martha stewart  Transfer to a paper towel lined rack to drain.
In the recipe beer battered onion rings by martha stewart  Sprinkle with salt.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  In a small bowl  combine the sour_cream  lime_juice  lime_zest  and salt and mix well.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  In another bowl  combine the red_cabbage  green_cabbage  jalapeño  2 tablespoons of the sour_cream sauce mix  lime_juice and salt.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  Mix until fully incorporated.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  Season the shrimp with a big pinch of salt.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  Combine flour  garlic_powder  smoked_paprika  cayenne  salt and baking_powder in a medium size bowl and mix well.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  Add beer and stir well.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  Add shrimp into the batter  making sure each is fully coated.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  Fry the shrimp in batches for 4 - 5 minutes  or until golden brown.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  Transfer the shrimp to a paper towel-lined plate.
In the recipe beer battered shrimp tacos  Top a tortilla with guacamole  rainbow coleslaw  fried shrimp  a drizzle of sour_cream sauce  sliced radishes  and cilantro.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  In a large skillet  brown the bratwurst on both sides over medium high heat.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  Add both cans of beer to the skillet.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  Simmer over medium-low heat for 20 minutes.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  Remove bratwurst from skillet and set aside.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  Continuing to simmer beer over medium low  add cream_cheese and cheddar cheese to the skillet.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  Stir occasionally until mixture is smooth  about 5 minutes.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  Add cayenne and mustard to beer cheese  stirring to incorporate.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  Cover a large plate with a layer of tortilla chips.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  Top with beer cheese.
In the recipe beer brat nachos  Slice bratwurst and arrange over nachos and add desired amount of nacho fixings.
In the recipe beer cheese beer brats  Add beer and brats to sauce pan.
In the recipe beer cheese beer brats  Cook on medium high heat for 10-15 minutes.
In the recipe beer cheese beer brats  Place brats on grill and cook until done (probably another 10-15 min).
In the recipe beer cheese beer brats  With 1 cup (235 ml) of beer in the pot  add cream_cheese and cheddar.
In the recipe beer cheese beer brats  Stir until cheese is mixed.
In the recipe beer cheese beer brats  Add the cheese mixture on top of the beer brats.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Slice a small piece of your pizza_dough  roll it into a ball then flatten it out.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Toss the cheddar cheese with the corn starch until it’s evenly distributed.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  In a medium saucepan  bring 1⁄2 cup (120 ml) of beer to a simmer.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Add in the cheese and corn starch mixture and whisk until it begins to thicken.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Once thick  take off the heat.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Place a small spoonful of the beer cheese mixture in the center of the dough.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Pick up the top and bottom edges and bring them up and together.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Do the same with the left and right edges.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Continue bringing in the rest of the edges of the dough until it all meets in the center and there are no gaps for the cheese to leak out of during baking.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  When you’ve finished putting together your pretzel bites  add the baking_soda to the water and immediately scoop in your pretzel bites.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Boil for 20-30 seconds
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Take out and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  In a small bowl  combine one egg and two tablespoons of beer and beat with a fork until they are well blended.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Brush the mixture onto the top of each pretzel bite  then top with coarse_salt.
In the recipe beer cheese pretzel bites  Bake for 15-20 minutes (or until they have browned).
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Cut rind off soft_cheeses while they are still chilled  then cut into cubes.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Blend cheeses with fork  then add cream_cheese  beer  spices  and diced onion and mix again.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  When well incorporated  stir in salt & pepper to taste.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Chill.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Take pizza_dough out of package and roll into a ball.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  In a large bowl  add beer and flour to the dough and mix with hands until firm and not sticky.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Rip off a piece of dough and roll it into a 6-inch (15 cm) long log.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  To form the pretzel  pull the ends of the log to the top of the circle.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Twist the ends around each other once and bring them down to meet the bottom of the circle.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Then transfer to a baking sheet.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Repeat until all dough is used.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Chill pretzels in the fridge for 20 minutes.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Add the baking_soda to the water and immediately add pretzels.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Boil for 20-30 seconds  then take out and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Brush egg wash onto the top of each pretzel  then top with coarse salt.
In the recipe beer pretzels with beer cheese dip  Bake for 15-20 minutes or until deep brown.
