In the recipe carrot chickpea burgers  Add lemon_juice and blend again until well-combined.
In the recipe carrot chickpea burgers  Scoop out a handful of the mixture and form into patties.
In the recipe carrot chickpea burgers  Cook the patty 4-5 minutes on each side  or until golden brown.
In the recipe carrot chickpea burgers  Assemble with your favorite burger toppings.
In the recipe carrot chickpea veggie burger  In a food processor  combine chickpeas  oats  carrots  red_onion  egg  salt  pepper  garlic_powder  and olive_oil.
In the recipe carrot chickpea veggie burger  Blend just until combined.
In the recipe carrot chickpea veggie burger  Add lemon_juice and blend again until well-combined.
In the recipe carrot chickpea veggie burger  Scoop out a handful of the mixture and form into patties.
In the recipe carrot chickpea veggie burger  Cook the patty 4-5 minutes on each side  or until golden brown.
In the recipe carrot chickpea veggie burger  Assemble with your favorite burger toppings.
In the recipe carrot corn fritters  Drain the carrots and let cool in a medium mixing bowl.
In the recipe carrot corn fritters  Once cool add Parmesan cheese  egg  flour  corn  parsley  and salt to a bowl and mix until the mixture has a semi-creamy texture.
In the recipe carrot corn fritters  Use a spoon to scoop out medium dollops of the carrot mixture and place it in the pan.
In the recipe carrot corn fritters  Let cook on each side for about 3 minutes  or until golden brown.
In the recipe carrot corn fritters  Remove from pan and place on paper towel to absorb excess oil.

In the recipe carrot dogs 4 ways  In a medium bowl  combine the vegetable_broth  apple cider  soy_sauce  maple_syrup  liquid_smoke  mustard_powder  paprika  ground_coriander  garlic_powder  and pepper.
In the recipe carrot dogs 4 ways  Place the carrots into a baking dish and pour the marinade on top.
In the recipe carrot dogs 4 ways  Let marinate for at least 30 minutes.
In the recipe carrot dogs 4 ways  If baking  cover the baking dish with aluminum foil and bake for about 40 minutes.
In the recipe carrot dogs 4 ways  Remove the foil and bake for another 25 minutes  until the carrots are just tender enough to be poked with a knife.
In the recipe carrot dogs 4 ways  If grilling  heat the olive_oil on a grill pan on high heat.
In the recipe carrot dogs 4 ways  Add the marinated carrots to the pan and spoon a bit of the marinade over.
In the recipe carrot dogs 4 ways  Cook for about 2 minutes on each side  until slightly charred.
In the recipe carrot dogs 4 ways  Place the carrots in buns and add your desired toppings.
In the recipe carrot fries  Cut carrots into fries and combine in a large bowl with olive_oil  parsley  paprika  salt  and pepper.
In the recipe carrot fries  Place on baking sheet lined with parchment paper in a single layer.
In the recipe carrot fries  Bake for 20-25 minutes  flipping halfway.
In the recipe carrot mango tango baby food 9 months  Add apples  carrots  mango  and water  breast milk  or formula to a blender or food processor.
In the recipe carrot mango tango baby food 9 months  Blend very well.
In the recipe carrot mango tango baby food 9 months  Refrigerate up to 3 days or freeze up to 1 month.
In the recipe carrot orange ginger juice  Add the orange  carrot  and ginger to a blender  and blend until smooth.
In the recipe carrot orange ginger juice  Using a mesh strainer  strain the juice over a large liquid measuring cup to remove the pulp.
In the recipe carrot orange ginger juice  Use a spoon to help stir the pulp and press out the liquid.
In the recipe carrot orange ginger juice  Chill the juice for at least 30 minutes (and keep up to 3 days).
In the recipe carrot sesame shrimp stir fry  Heat 1 tablespoon of sesame_oil in a large  nonstick skillet over medium heat.
In the recipe carrot sesame shrimp stir fry  Pour in the shrimp and season with 1⁄4 teaspoon of the salt.
In the recipe carrot sesame shrimp stir fry  Fry the shrimp for 1 minute on each side.
In the recipe carrot sesame shrimp stir fry  Remove the shrimp from the pan and pour in the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil.
In the recipe carrot sesame shrimp stir fry  Toss in the carrots and remaining 1⁄4 teaspoon of salt and sauté for a few minutes until they begin to soften.
In the recipe carrot sesame shrimp stir fry  Add in the snow peas  garlic  and soy_sauce and sauté until the garlic becomes fragrant  about 30 seconds.

In the recipe carrot sesame shrimp stir fry  Toss the shrimp back into the pan  sprinkle on the sesame_seeds  and mix until everything is well incorporated and the shrimp is fully cooked  about 1 minute.
In the recipe carrot sesame shrimp stir fry  Divide the mixture evenly between 4 bowls and sprinkle with a few more sesame_seeds  if desired.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  In a medium bowl  combine the soy_sauce  hoisin_sauce  rice_vinegar  honey  sesame_oil  ginger  and garlic.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  Set aside.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  In a medium bowl  season the chicken with salt  pepper  and cornstarch.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  Heat a 9.5" fry pan over medium-high heat and add sesame_oil.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  Add the chicken and cook for 5-6 minutes  or until the chicken begins to brown.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  Remove chicken and set aside in a separate bowl.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  Add the broccoli and bell_peppers  and cook for 2-3 minutes.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  Add the chicken  cashews and sauce.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  Stir together and allow sauce to thicken.
In the recipe cashew chicken stir fry  Remove from heat and serve over brown_rice.
In the recipe cashew coconut bars  Add the cashews  dates  coconut  salt  coconut_milk  and vanilla to a food processor and pulse until the mixture starts to clump together.
In the recipe cashew coconut bars  Transfer the mixture to the prepared baking dish and press into an even layer.
In the recipe cashew coconut bars  Top with more coconut  if desired.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Add the chicken_stock to a microwave-safe liquid measuring cup and microwave on high power for 3 minutes  until hot.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Stir in the saffron threads and set aside.
In the recipe cast iron paella  On a cutting board  pat the shrimp dry with paper towels.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and the pepper on both sides and set aside.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Heat the olive_oil in a 12-inch (30 cm) cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat until it begins to shimmer.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Add the chorizo and cook  stirring  until browned in spots  3 minutes.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Add the onion and cook until softened  about 3 minutes.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Add the garlic and paprika and cook  stirring  until aromatic  about 30 seconds.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Add the rice and stir until lightly toasted  1 minute.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Add the tomatoes and reserved chicken_stock and stir to combine.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Cook without stirring until the rice is al dente  15 minutes.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Remove the lid and arrange the shrimp  mussels  and peas on top of the rice.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Cover and increase the heat to medium-high.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Remove the lid and pour the lemon_juice over the paella.
In the recipe cast iron paella  Sprinkle with the remaining teaspoon of salt and the parsley and serve.
In the recipe catalina salad dressing  Add the ingredients into a mason jar.
In the recipe catalina salad dressing  Screw the lid on tightly and shake vigorously.
In the recipe catalina salad dressing  Pour over your favorite salad ingredients and enjoy!
In the recipe cauliflower alfredo  Add the cauliflower_florets.
In the recipe cauliflower alfredo  Cover the pot and boil for 5-7 minutes  or until cauliflower is soft.
In the recipe cauliflower alfredo  With a slotted spoon  add the cooked cauliflower to a blender.
In the recipe cauliflower alfredo  Add the milk  butter  garlic  salt  and pepper and blend until smooth.
In the recipe cauliflower alfredo  Toss the cooked_pasta with cauliflower alfredo.
In the recipe cauliflower alfredo  Serve topped with parmesan  and parsley.
In the recipe cauliflower cheddar fritters  Once cool add cheddar cheese  egg  flour  green_onion and salt to a bowl and mix until the mixture has a semi-creamy texture.
In the recipe cauliflower cheddar fritters  Use a spoon to scoop out medium dollops of mixture and place it in the pan.
In the recipe cauliflower cheddar fritters  Let cook on each side for about 3 minutes  or until golden brown.
In the recipe cauliflower chickpea burgers  Place a towel over a large bowl.
In the recipe cauliflower chickpea burgers  Using a box grater  grate the head of cauliflower down to the stem over the bowl.
In the recipe cauliflower chickpea burgers  Add the salt to the cauliflower  mix it in  and allow it to sit for 20 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower chickpea burgers  After 20 minutes  use the towel to wring out the excess water from the cauliflower and return it to the bowl.
In the recipe cauliflower chickpea burgers  Add the chickpeas  onion  bell_pepper  garlic  cilantro  and spices to the cauliflower.
In the recipe cauliflower chickpea burgers  Using a potato masher  mash the ingredients until thoroughly mixed together.
In the recipe cauliflower chickpea burgers  Take a quarter of the mixture and shape it into a patty using your hands.
In the recipe cauliflower chickpea burgers  Take the patties and place them on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet and bake for 20 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower chickpea burgers  Place patties on buns  and top with hummus  lettuce  tomato  and pickles.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Using a food processor or a cheese grater  grate the cauliflower until fine or “riced.”
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Transfer the riced cauliflower to a large microwave-safe bowl  sprinkle with salt and microwave for 5 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Allow cauliflower to cool and transfer into a second bowl lined with a thin towel (cheesecloth and paper towels will also work).
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Wrap the cauliflower tightly and squeeze out the liquid.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Return the cauliflower to your large bowl and add olive_oil  garlic_powder  onion  parmesan  salt  pepper  and 2 of the eggs.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Combine well.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Line a lightly greased muffin tin with the cauliflower mixture  using your fingers to press it firmly into the bottom and sides  creating a crust.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Bake for 20-30 minutes  or until the crust turns golden brown.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Pour the remaining whisked eggs evenly into the cauliflower cups  then add toppings of your choice.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  We used tomatoes and basil  spinach and mushrooms  and broccoli and cheddar_cheese.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Bake an additional 15-20 minutes or until eggs are cooked through.
In the recipe cauliflower crust egg cups  Allow to cool slightly before serving.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Remove the leaves and stem of the cauliflower.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Transfer pieces to a food processor and rice the cauliflower by pulsing it in the food processor  or by shredding it on a box grater.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Once riced  transfer to a large bowl and microwave for 4 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Let it cool down for a few minutes before handling!
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Transfer cooked cauliflower to a clean towel and wring out as much liquid as possible.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Place wrung cauliflower in a bowl and combine with mozzarella  oregano  basil  salt  garlic_powder  and an egg.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Mix well.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Place cauliflower mixture in the middle.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Spread out the mixture and form a circle out of the cauliflower mixture  pushing along the edge to raise a “crust.”
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Bake for 15 minutes  or until the crust has become golden brown in the center and on the edges.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Top with your favorite pizza sauce and toppings  being careful not to overload the pizza.
In the recipe cauliflower crust pizza  Bake for another 5-7 minutes  or until the cheese has fully melted.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  Add the cauliflower to the bowl of a food processor and pulse until finely crumbled.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  Place in microwave-safe dish and microwave for 5 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  Place cooked cauliflower into a towel and squeeze out as much water as possible.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  Add the cauliflower to a bowl with 1 egg  parmesan_cheese  garlic_powder  and 1⁄4 teaspoon salt in a bowl.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  Press crust mixture evenly into tart plate  making sure to go up the sides of the plate.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  In a separate bowl  whisk together 5 eggs  milk  crumbled feta_cheese  1⁄2 teaspoon salt  and pepper.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  In a medium skillet  heat olive_oil over medium heat.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  Add asparagus pieces and cook until slightly tender.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  Add the spinach and cook until wilted.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  Place asparagus and spinach mixture on the bottom of the cooked cauliflower crust.
In the recipe cauliflower crusted quiche  Pour egg and cheese mixture over the top and sprinkle with green_onions.
In the recipe cauliflower fritter  Mash cauliflower  mix in salt  pepper  garlic  onions  parsley  flour  grated parmesan and egg.
In the recipe cauliflower fritter  From patties with the mashed cauliflower mix.
In the recipe cauliflower fritter  Coat both sides of patties with wheat_flour.
In the recipe cauliflower fritter  Fry in oil until golden brown and crispy on both sides.
In the recipe cauliflower fritter  Add sour_cream or chives to taste.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Add the cauliflower to a steamer basket set over a medium pot of boiling water.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Cover and steam for 10 minutes  or until fork-tender.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Transfer the cauliflower to a clean dish towel and squeeze the excess water into a bowl.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Transfer the squeezed cauliflower to a food processor.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Add the flour  salt  and olive_oil and pulse until the dough forms a ball.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Transfer the dough to a lightly floured surface and knead for 3-4 minutes  or until the dough bounces back when poked.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Shape the dough into a ball  then cut into 4 equal pieces
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Working 1 piece at a time  cut in half again  then roll out a rope about 6 inches (3-cm) long and 1 inch (2-cm) wide.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Slice each rope into 1⁄2-inch (1-cm) pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Roll each piece along the back of a fork to create a line pattern.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Transfer the gnocchi to a large pot of salted boiling water.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Boil until the gnocchi float to the surface  3-5 minutes  then remove with a slotted spoon.
In the recipe cauliflower gnocchi  Toss the gnocchi with pesto_sauce and serve immediately.
In the recipe cauliflower grilled cheese  Grate a cauliflower over a large bowl.
In the recipe cauliflower grilled cheese  Sprinkle a pinch of salt over the grated cauliflower and mix evenly.
In the recipe cauliflower grilled cheese  Leave to sit for 20 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower grilled cheese  Pour the cauliflower into a clean kitchen towel and wring the water out.
In the recipe cauliflower grilled cheese  In a large bowl  combine the cauliflower  and remaining ingredients  (except your cheese and toppings) stir until well mixed.
In the recipe cauliflower grilled cheese  Using a spoon transfer two hearty scoops of mixture to form each “bread slice” onto a skillet on medium-low heat for about 10 minutes  each side.
In the recipe cauliflower grilled cheese  Add your cheese and any other toppings  allow a couple minutes for cheese to melt.
In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Using a coarse grater  grate the cauliflower until the entire head has crumbled down into small bit.
In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Transfer the cauliflower bits to a bowl and sprinkle over a 1⁄2 teaspoon of the salt.
In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Mix the cauliflower to incorporate the salt and let sit for 20 minutes to draw out moisture.
In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Transfer the soaking cauliflower to another bowl lined with a large towel.
In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Wrap the towel closed and squeeze so that all of the excess liquid is strained.

In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Transfer the cauliflower back into the first bowl used and mix with the cheese  chives  garlic  olive_oil  basil  black_pepper  eggs and remaining 1⁄2 teaspoon of salt.
In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Turnover a large roasting tray and line with parchment paper - this helps prevent burning on the bottom of the hash browns.
In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Divide the cauliflower mixture into 6 even portions  place on the tray  and shape into hash browns.
In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Bake for 35-40 minutes  until golden brown.
In the recipe cauliflower hash browns  Serve with desired dipping_sauce.
In the recipe cauliflower meat burrito bowl  Cut the cauliflower in half and break it into small florets.
In the recipe cauliflower meat burrito bowl  Place the florets in a food processor and pulse until they break down to rice-size pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower meat burrito bowl  Add the mushrooms to the food processor and pulse until broken down to rice-size pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower meat burrito bowl  Heat the olive_oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
In the recipe cauliflower meat burrito bowl  Add the onion and garlic to the pan and cook for about 4 minutes  until fragrant and the onion is translucent.
In the recipe cauliflower meat burrito bowl  Add the cauliflower  mushrooms  cumin  smoked_paprika  chili_powder  soy_sauce  salt  and pepper and stir.
In the recipe cauliflower meat burrito bowl  Cook for about 10 minutes  until the cauliflower and mushroom mixture is tender and the water released from the mushrooms has evaporated.
In the recipe cauliflower meat burrito bowl  Add the rice to a bowl and top with cauliflower “meat” and your favorite toppings.
In the recipe cauliflower meat burrito bowl  Serve with a lime_wedge and garnish with cilantro.
In the recipe cauliflower meat nachos  Cut the cauliflower in half and break it into small florets.
In the recipe cauliflower meat nachos  Place the florets in a food processor and pulse until they break down to rice-size pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower meat nachos  Add the mushrooms to the food processor and pulse until broken down to rice-size pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower meat nachos  Heat the olive_oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
In the recipe cauliflower meat nachos  Add the onion and garlic to the pan and cook for about 4 minutes  until fragrant and the onion is translucent.
In the recipe cauliflower meat nachos  Add the cauliflower  mushrooms  cumin  smoked_paprika  chili_powder  soy_sauce  salt  and pepper and stir.
In the recipe cauliflower meat nachos  Cook for about 10 minutes  until the cauliflower and mushroom mixture is tender and the water released from the mushrooms has evaporated.
In the recipe cauliflower meat nachos  Load with the cauliflower “meat” and other toppings of your choice.
In the recipe cauliflower meat nachos  Let cool for 5 minutes  then garnish with cilantro and serve.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Cut the cauliflower in half and break it into small florets.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Place the florets in a food processor and pulse until they break down to rice-size pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Add the mushrooms to the food processor and pulse until broken down to rice-size pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Heat the olive_oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Add the onion and garlic to the pan and cook for about 4 minutes  until fragrant and the onion is translucent.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Add the cauliflower  mushrooms  cumin  smoked_paprika  chili_powder  soy_sauce  salt  and pepper and stir.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Cook for about 10 minutes  until the cauliflower and mushroom mixture is tender and the water released from the mushrooms has evaporated.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Heat a tortilla over low heat in a large  greased skillet.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Sprinkle the tortilla with a layer of cheese  then add a layer of cauliflower “meat”  caramelized onions and peppers  and another layer of cheese.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Top with another tortilla and cook for about 4 minutes  until the bottom layer of cheese has melted and the bottom tortilla is golden brown.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Carefully flip the quesadilla and cook for another 4 minutes  until all of the cheese has melted.
In the recipe cauliflower meat quesadillas  Slice each tortilla into wedges and serve.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Cut the cauliflower in half and break it into small florets.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Place the florets in a food processor and pulse until they break down to rice-size pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Remove from the processor and set aside.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Add the mushrooms to the food processor and pulse until broken down to rice-size pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Heat the olive_oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Add the onion and garlic to the pan and cook for about 4 minutes  until fragrant and the onion is translucent.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Add the cauliflower  mushrooms  cumin  smoked_paprika  chili_powder  soy_sauce  salt  and pepper and stir.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Cook for about 10 minutes  until the cauliflower and mushroom mixture is tender and the water released from the mushrooms has evaporated.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Add the cauliflower “meat” to the tortilla  along with your favorite toppings.
In the recipe cauliflower meat tacos  Serve with a lime_wedge.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Melt butter on medium heat in a large pot.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Add the garlic and onion  and sauté 1-2 minutes until onion is translucent.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Stir in salt and pepper.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Add the cauliflower  vegetable_broth  and water  then stir.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Bring to a boil.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Add the thyme then cover and reduce to a simmer for 15 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Uncover and remove the thyme.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Use an immersion or countertop blender to blend the soup until smooth.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Mix in vegetarian Parmesan and chives.
In the recipe cauliflower parmesan soup  Allow to cool 2 minutes then serve.
In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Add the cauliflower to the bowl of a food processor  and pulse until it becomes the size of rice.
In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Place the cauliflower in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave on high for 3 minutes  or until it begins to steam.
In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Remove the cauliflower and place on a clean kitchen towel.
In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Wrap the towel around the cauliflower  and squeeze out as much liquid as possible.
In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Discard the liquid and transfer the cauliflower to a bowl.
In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Add the Parmesan  egg  salt  almond flour  and oregano to the bowl with the cauliflower.
In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Stir to combine.

In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Transfer the mixture to a parchment paper-lined baking sheet and use your hands to form it into a round disk  1⁄2-inch (1 cm) thick and 10-inches (25 cm) in diameter.
In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Bake the crust for 25 to 30 minutes  or until the crust begins to brown.
In the recipe cauliflower pizza crust  Top the crust with marinara sauce  mozzarella  and basil  or other toppings of your choice  and bake for 10 more minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower potato salad  Slice cauliflower into small florets.
In the recipe cauliflower potato salad  Place cauliflower onto baking sheet and season with salt  pepper  and olive_oil.
In the recipe cauliflower potato salad  Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and a bit crispy.
In the recipe cauliflower potato salad  In a large bowl  combine all dressing ingredients.
In the recipe cauliflower potato salad  Set aside.
In the recipe cauliflower potato salad  Dice eggs  onion  and celery.
In the recipe cauliflower potato salad  In a large bowl  combine cauliflower  eggs  onion  celery  and dressing.
In the recipe cauliflower potato salad  Garnish with more freshly chopped dill before serving.
In the recipe cauliflower rice chicken bake  In a large bowl add the cauliflower rice  broccoli  chicken  mozzarella  cheddar  garlic_powder  onion_powder  and salt.
In the recipe cauliflower rice chicken bake  Stir well to combine.
In the recipe cauliflower rice chicken bake  Add mixture to a baking pan then cover with aluminum foil.
In the recipe cauliflower rice chicken bake  Bake for 40 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower rice chicken bake  Uncover then top with remaining cheddar.
In the recipe cauliflower rice chicken bake  Bake for 10 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower rice chicken bake  Remove and allow to cool for 5-10 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower rice chicken bake  Garnish with parsley  if desired and serve.
In the recipe cauliflower shrimp fried rice  Pulse cauliflower in a food processor until broken into rice-sized pieces.
In the recipe cauliflower shrimp fried rice  Heat the sesame_oil in a large skillet or wok.
In the recipe cauliflower shrimp fried rice  Toss in the carrots and sauté until soft  about 5 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower shrimp fried rice  Add in the garlic and shrimp and sautée until the shrimp begin to turn pink  about 2 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower shrimp fried rice  Add the peas and cauliflower rice and mix until the cauliflower has warmed through.
In the recipe cauliflower shrimp fried rice  Move the contents of the pan to the side to create a well in the center.
In the recipe cauliflower shrimp fried rice  Pour in the eggs and slowly scraped the cooked bits off the bottom of the pan to scramble the eggs.
In the recipe cauliflower shrimp fried rice  Once the eggs are almost finished cooking  mix everything in the pan together.
In the recipe cauliflower shrimp fried rice  Season the cauliflower with white_pepper and soy_sauce  give one last good mix to combine and serve with a garnish of sliced green_onion.
In the recipe cauliflower soup  Blend cauliflower  pepper  and 1 cup (235 ml) of cauliflower stock until a smooth consistency is reached.
In the recipe cauliflower soup  Transfer the cauliflower soup to a plate.
In the recipe cauliflower steaks  Remove the green leaves from the cauliflower stem with a knife.
In the recipe cauliflower steaks  Place the cauliflower core-down on a cutting board and trim 2 sides so they become flat.
In the recipe cauliflower steaks  Cut the cauliflower in half and then cut each half in two to get 4 “steaks”.
In the recipe cauliflower steaks  Rinse and dry the cauliflower steaks.
In the recipe cauliflower steaks  In a small bowl  combine the olive_oil  lemon_juice  basil  oregano  thyme  rosemary  onion  and garlic  plus salt and pepper to taste.
In the recipe cauliflower steaks  Mix well.
In the recipe cauliflower steaks  Place the cauliflower steaks on the baking sheet and brush generously with the oil mixture.
In the recipe cauliflower steaks  Bake for about 25 minutes  flipping halfway  until tender.
In the recipe cauliflower steaks  Serve as desired  such as on a sandwich with pesto and red pepper  or with barbecue sauce and roasted potatoes  or with vegan mushroom gravy and lentils.
In the recipe cauliflower tortilla tacos  Pulse in a food processor until cauliflower is finer than rice.
In the recipe cauliflower tortilla tacos  Place in a bowl and salt  to taste.
In the recipe cauliflower tortilla tacos  Microwave for 4 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower tortilla tacos  Drain the cauliflower using a kitchen towel and squeeze out all the excess water.
In the recipe cauliflower tortilla tacos  After draining add the cauliflower into a bowl and mix in the eggs  lime_juice  pepper  dried_oregano  paprika  and chili_powder.
In the recipe cauliflower tortilla tacos  Mix together.
In the recipe cauliflower tortilla tacos  Roll out 6 balls of the mixture and then press onto a baking sheet.
In the recipe cauliflower tortilla tacos  Bake for 10 minutes  flip and then bake for another 10 minutes  or until edges are crispy.
In the recipe cauliflower tortilla tacos  After cooling  fill with your desired fillings
In the recipe cauliflower tots  Aggressively season it with salt.
In the recipe cauliflower tots  Blanch the cauliflower in boiling water for about 5 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower tots  Drain and finely chop the cooked cauliflower.
In the recipe cauliflower tots  In a mixing bowl  add cauliflower  egg  bread crumbs  cheddar_cheese  parmesan_cheese  garlic  and salt.
In the recipe cauliflower tots  Chill in the refrigerator for 15-20 minutes.
In the recipe cauliflower tots  Shape the mixture into tot shapes and spread them evenly on the sheet.
In the recipe cauliflower tots  Bake for 10 minutes at 400°F (200°C).
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Add the butter and leave to melt and foam for a minute or so.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Next add the onions  mushrooms  garlic  salt and pepper.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Slowly cook for around 10 minutes whilst continually stirring.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Take the celery sticks and peel the top ridged side to remove some of the stringy texture.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Then cut into a small dice.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Place the onions and mushrooms back onto the heat and add the diced celery.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Stir for around a minute to warm through the celery and coat it with all the meaty flavour of the mushrooms and butter.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Next add to mushroom and celery mixture to mash potato and mix to combine.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Once combined take around a tablespoon of mixture and form into a croquette shape.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  To coat the croquettes  coat each croquet in flour  making sure to dust the excess off.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Then dip in egg  then breadcrumbs.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Place back into the eggs then back into the bread crumbs to give an extra thick and crunchy coating.
In the recipe celery mushroom croquettes  Carefully place the croquettes into the oil and cook for 2-3 minutes or until golden brown.
In the recipe cereal poke cupcakes  Fill cupcake wrappers 1⁄4-full with cake batter.
In the recipe cereal poke cupcakes  Bake cupcakes according to whatever batter is being used.
In the recipe cereal poke cupcakes  In a gallon-sized bag  crush cereal into small crumbs.
In the recipe cereal poke cupcakes  In a large bowl  combine cereal crumbs and butter.
In the recipe cereal poke cupcakes  Using the small end of a spatula  poke holes in the cupcakes.
In the recipe cereal poke cupcakes  Fill holes with sweetened_condensed_milk.
In the recipe cereal poke cupcakes  Top cupcakes with cereal crumb mixture and pack down with a spoon  creating a uniform crust.
In the recipe cereal poke cupcakes  Individually wrap cupcakes in plastic_wrap.
In the recipe cereal poke cupcakes  Chill cupcakes in cooler or refrigerator until ready to eat.
In the recipe chai spiced cheesecake muffins  Make the muffin batter: In a large bowl  whisk together the flour  cinnamon  ginger  cardamom  nutmeg  baking_soda  and salt with a fork.
In the recipe chai spiced cheesecake muffins  In a separate large bowl  combine the applesauce  brown_sugar  eggs  vanilla  and vegetable_oil.
In the recipe chai spiced cheesecake muffins  Mix with a fork  then gradually incorporate the dry ingredients until the batter is thick and smooth.
In the recipe chai spiced cheesecake muffins  Make the cheesecake filling: In a medium bowl  use a fork to mix together the cream_cheese  sugar  and vanilla until fluffy and smooth.
In the recipe chai spiced cheesecake muffins  Grease a 2 12-cup muffin tin with nonstick spray.
In the recipe chai spiced cheesecake muffins  Scoop about 1⁄4 cup (30 g) of muffin batter into each cup.
In the recipe chai spiced cheesecake muffins  Add a teaspoon of cheesecake filling to the center of each cup.
In the recipe chai spiced cheesecake muffins  Use a toothpick to swirl the cheesecake into the batter.
In the recipe chai spiced cheesecake muffins  Bake for 18 minutes  or until the muffins are springy and lightly browned around the edges.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  In a large bowl  combine the polenta  almond_flour  baking_powder  baking_soda  and salt.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  Stir well.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  Zest and juice the orange.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  Add the orange_zest and juice to a separate large bowl with the eggs  olive_oil  maple_syrup  vanilla  cardamom  cinnamon  nutmeg  and cloves.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  Whisk well to combine.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and gently fold with a rubber spatula until fully incorporated.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  Fold in the diced plums.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  Pour the batter into the prepared pan.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  Arrange the sliced plum decoratively on top of the cake in a circular pattern.
In the recipe chai spiced plum polenta cake  Bake the cake for 50-55 minutes  until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
In the recipe champagne jello shots  Boil two cups of water.
In the recipe champagne jello shots  Mix 4 packets of unflavored_gelatin into the water.
In the recipe champagne jello shots  Let cool for a few minutes.
In the recipe champagne jello shots  Add one bottle of cream or vanilla soda  and 3⁄4 of a bottle of champagne.
In the recipe champagne jello shots  Cover and refrigerate 3-5 hours.
In the recipe champagne jello shots  Top with sprinkles and/or pop rocks  directly before serving!
In the recipe charcoal ice cream  In a large freezer bag  place a piece of dry_ice.
In the recipe charcoal ice cream  Close the plastic bag  but leave a one-inch opening to prevent the bag from fill with gas.
In the recipe charcoal ice cream  Cover the bag with a kitchen towel and carefully use a kitchen mallet to break the dry_ice into a powder.

In the recipe charcoal ice cream  In a large bowl  combine heavy_cream  half & half  sugar  activate charcoal (avoid consuming more than 100 grams of activated charcoal)  2 tablespoons mint_extract  and at least 4 tablespoons black_food_coloring (more food coloring might be
In the recipe charcoal ice cream  Whisk together ice cream mixture until frothy.
In the recipe charcoal ice cream  Slowly add a spoonful of dry_ice into the mixture and whisk together.
In the recipe charcoal ice cream  Gradually add and mix in dry_ice until a solid consistency is achieved.
In the recipe charcoal ice cream  Wait for all the dry_ice to evaporate before consuming.
In the recipe checkerboard cake  Cut both cakes in half widthwise to create four cakes.
In the recipe checkerboard cake  Place a small plate on top of the cake and cut around to create a smaller circle.
In the recipe checkerboard cake  Place a glass in the middle of the cake and cut around to create an even smaller circle.
In the recipe checkerboard cake  Insert the next yellow cake ring and then the inner chocolate_cake ring.
In the recipe checkerboard cake  Frost the cake with a thin layer of frosting in between each layer.
In the recipe checkerboard cake  Continue forming layers alternating the colors on the outside.
In the recipe checkerboard cake  After the fourth layer frost the entire cake and cool in the refrigerator.
In the recipe checkerboard cake  Slice and serve.
In the recipe cheddar and sour cream cheese bites  In a food processor  or by hand  crush 1⁄2 a box of Triscuits.
In the recipe cheddar and sour cream cheese bites  Set aside.
In the recipe cheddar and sour cream cheese bites  Combine all of the filling ingredients in a large bowl.
In the recipe cheddar and sour cream cheese bites  Pinch off bite sized balls of filling and roll between your hands (about 1 oz or 28g each).
In the recipe cheddar and sour cream cheese bites  Roll the balls in the crushed Triscuit mixture  then coat it in beaten egg  then again in Triscuit mixture.
In the recipe cheddar and sour cream cheese bites  Fry each bite until Triscuit coating turns a light brown  about 45 seconds.
In the recipe cheddar and sour cream cheese bites  Garnish with more chopped dill and a squeeze of lemon.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Combine cheese  bacon pieces  jalapeños  and ranch in a bowl.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Stir together and refrigerate.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Season the ground_beef with salt and pepper in a large bowl  and mix in with your hands.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Grab a baseball-sized piece of beef.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Roll it with your hands into a ball and place on a parchment lined baking tray.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Using a clean  empty soda or beer can  press the ball of beef around the can to create a bowl.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Make sure to smooth out any cracks.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Fill the bowls with the cheddar mixture and refrigerate for 2 hours.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Cook burger bowls over indirect heat for 25-30 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar bacon ranch burger bowls  Serve with or without a bun with your favorite toppings.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Make the filling: Melt the butter in a large cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Add the the flour and whisk until bubbling.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Whisk in the milk until smooth  then add the chicken  peas and carrots  pearl onions  potato  salt  and pepper.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Stir until everything is well coated  then continue to cook until the filling is bubbling and the liquid has thickened slightly  7-10 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Make the biscuits: In a large bowl  stir together the flour  baking_powder  baking_soda  and salt.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Using your a fork  your hands  or a pastry cutter  work the butter into the dry ingredients  leaving pea-sized chunks.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Add the buttermilk and fold with a rubber spatula until a thick dough comes together.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Bring the dough together into one large mass  then roll out with a rolling pin to about 1 1⁄2-2 inches (4-5 centimeters) thick.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Using a 2-3-inch (5-7 centimeter) biscuit cutter or small glass dipped in flour  cut out rounds from the dough.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Cut out all of the rounds  then place on top of the filling so the dough does not warm too much.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Brush tops of the biscuits with the beaten egg and top with cheddar cheese.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Bake for 25-30 minutes  until the biscuits are golden brown and cooked through.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Carefully remove from the oven and let cool for 10 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar biscuit chicken pot pie  Garnish with chives before serving.
In the recipe cheddar chips  Place cheddar crackers into a ziplock bag and crush them so that they reach a powdery state.
In the recipe cheddar chips  In a large bowl  mix the potato chips with oil  cheddar powder  and salt.
In the recipe cheddar chips  Arrange chips on greased baking sheet
In the recipe cheddar chips  Bake for 30-35 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar chive hash browns  Peel and grate the potatoes  and soak them in ice water.
In the recipe cheddar chive hash browns  Squeeze out excess water and place potatoes in a bowl.
In the recipe cheddar chive hash browns  Add the rest of the ingredients to the bowl and mix well.
In the recipe cheddar chive hash browns  On a nonstick pan  form patties of the potato mixture with your hands.
In the recipe cheddar chive hash browns  Bake for 35-40 minutes or until brown and crispy.
In the recipe cheddar corn fritters  In a large bowl add the ingredients.
In the recipe cheddar corn fritters  Mix well.
In the recipe cheddar corn fritters  Spoon 2 tablespoons of mixture to form each fritter into the hot oil.
In the recipe cheddar corn fritters  Flip after about a minute and a half or when you can see the edges beginning to brown.
In the recipe cheddar corn fritters  Repeat for other side.
In the recipe cheddar corn fritters  Serve with a dollop of sour cream and chives.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Add 2 cups (200 g) of cheddar cheese and the butter to a large bowl.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Mix to combine with an electric hand mixer or stand mixer.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Add the flour  paprika  garlic_powder  and 2 teaspoons salt and mix well.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Add 3 tablespoons of ice_water and mix.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Add the remaining ice_water 1 tablespoon at a time.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Transfer the dough to a clean surface and knead with your hands until it comes together.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Shape the dough into a disc  then wrap in plastic wrap and chill in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Lightly flour a clean surface and roll out the dough into a circle about 1⁄8 inch (8 mm) thick.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Carefully transfer the crust to a 91⁄2-inch (24-cm) glass pie dish.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Trim the edges (save the trimmings to make crackers!).
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Poke holes in the bottom of the crust with a fork  then use the tines to crimp the edges.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Line the dough with parchment paper and fill with pie weights.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Bake for 30 minutes  until the edges are crisp.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  In a large skillet over medium-high heat  cook the bacon until crisp  5-7 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Using tongs  remove the bacon from the skillet and let drain on paper towels until cool enough to handle.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Add the broccoli to the skillet and cook until lightly browned  about 5 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Chop the bacon.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Remove the pie weights from the crust  then add the broccoli and chopped bacon to the center.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Sprinkle with the remaining shredded_cheddar_cheese.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  In a medium bowl  lightly beat the eggs.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Add the milk  remaining 1⁄2 teaspoon salt  and the pepper.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Whisk to combine.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Pour the egg mixture over the fillings in the crust.
In the recipe cheddar crusted bacon broccoli quiche  Bake for 35-40 minutes  or until the eggs are set and the top is lightly browned.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  Place cheese crackers in a resealable bag and crush with a rolling pin until they become finely ground.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  Roll each chicken piece into flour and then coat into eggs.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  Place each chicken piece in the cracker crumbs.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  Coat the chicken with the crumbs.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  In a medium bowl  combine broccoli and potatoes.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  Add olive_oil  rosemary  garlic  salt and pepper.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  Toss until vegetables are well-coated.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  Arrange vegetables on parchment-lined baking sheet.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  Bake chicken and veggies for 35-40 minutes or until chicken is golden brown and cooked through.
In the recipe cheddar oven fried chicken  Top chicken with parsley and serve.

In the recipe cheddar parmesan cauliflower bites  Wrap cauliflower in a clean dish towel  then turn it upside down and bang it against the surface of your counter until you feel the cauliflower crack (be sure to rotate to break it up on all sides).
In the recipe cheddar parmesan cauliflower bites  Pull florets off of stem and break apart the bigger florets into smaller pieces.
In the recipe cheddar parmesan cauliflower bites  Microwave florets for 4 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar parmesan cauliflower bites  In one small bowl  pour flour; in another  whisk two eggs; and in a medium bowl  combine your bread crumbs  Parmesan cheese  and cheddar_cheese.
In the recipe cheddar parmesan cauliflower bites  Coat each piece in flour  followed by the eggs and finally the bread crumb mixture.
In the recipe cheddar parmesan cauliflower bites  Spray a baking sheet and place all cauliflower bites in it  then drizzle olive_oil over them or spray with cooking spray.
In the recipe cheddar parmesan cauliflower bites  Bake in the oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
In the recipe cheddar parmesan cauliflower bites  Serve with marinara  ranch  or sour cream.
In the recipe cheddar ranch chicken strips  On a cutting board  slice chicken_breasts against the grain into strips.
In the recipe cheddar ranch chicken strips  Place the chicken strips in a bowl and add in buttermilk and ranch packet.
In the recipe cheddar ranch chicken strips  Stir until well-coated.
In the recipe cheddar ranch chicken strips  Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator for at least an hour.
In the recipe cheddar ranch chicken strips  Pour cheese crackers into a resealable bag and crush with a rolling pin until they become finely ground.
In the recipe cheddar ranch chicken strips  Open the bag and place a marinated piece of chicken in the cracker crumbs.
In the recipe cheddar ranch chicken strips  Coat the chicken with the crumbs and place on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet.
In the recipe cheddar ranch chicken strips  Bake for 20 minutes  flipping halfway.
In the recipe cheddar ranch popcorn chicken  Chop chicken_breasts into bite-size pieces.
In the recipe cheddar ranch popcorn chicken  In a large bowl  combine chicken  buttermilk  and ranch packet.
In the recipe cheddar ranch popcorn chicken  Refrigerate for 2 hours.
In the recipe cheddar ranch popcorn chicken  In a large ziplock bag  crumble the cheese crackers into desired crumbs (to replace bread crumbs).
In the recipe cheddar ranch popcorn chicken  Place cracker crumbs into a medium bowl and coat each piece of chicken until fully covered.
In the recipe cheddar ranch popcorn chicken  Heat oil to 350°F (180°C) and fry chicken until crackers turn golden brown (3 minutes).
In the recipe cheddar ranch popcorn chicken  Place on a paper towel to dry.
In the recipe cheddar ranch popcorn chicken  Serve with a side of ranch or any sauce.
In the recipe cheddar ranch potato bake  Slice the potatoes in half  lengthwise  then slice each half lengthwise three times and across four times  to cube.
In the recipe cheddar ranch potato bake  Bring a large pot of water to a boil and drop in chopped potatoes  cook 10 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar ranch potato bake  Drain potatoes and mix in ranch  garlic_powder  paprika  salt  and pepper.
In the recipe cheddar ranch potato bake  Transfer to a 9x13-inch (23x33 cm) baking dish.
In the recipe cheddar ranch potato bake  Bake for 30-35 minutes  or until nicely browned.
In the recipe cheddar ranch potato bake  While still hot  mix in cheddar and chives.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Add the breakfast_sausage to a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Cook  breaking up with a spatula until no longer pink  7-8 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Add the white and light green scallions  1⁄2 of the bell_pepper  and 1⁄2 of the spinach.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Sauté for 2 minutes  until the spinach is wilted  then add the rest of the spinach and continue cooking until wilted.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  In a medium bowl  whisk together the eggs  salt  and garlic_powder.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Add the milk and whisk to incorporate.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Grease a 9 (22 cm) x 13-inch (33 cm) glass baking dish with nonstick spray.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Add the cubed bread to the baking dish.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Sprinkle 1 cup (100 G) of shredded cheese over the bread  then evenly spread the sausage mixture on top.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Pour the egg mixture over the sausage mixture.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Cover the baking dish with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour  or overnight.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  In a liquid measuring cup or small bowl  combine the chicken_stock and heavy_cream.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Pour over the chilled bake.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Sprinkle the remaining cup of cheese and remaining bell_pepper over the top.

In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes  then uncover and bake for another 15-20 minutes  until the custard is set and the cheese is golden brown.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Remove from oven and let cool for 15 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar sausage and egg breakfast bake  Garnish with the dark green scallions  then slice and serve.
In the recipe cheddar spoons  Using an electric hand mixer or stand mixer  beat the cheese  butter  and salt in a large bowl.
In the recipe cheddar spoons  Once combined  mix in the flour and add the ice_water one tablespoon at a time.
In the recipe cheddar spoons  The dough should hold together when pressed but crumble apart if you break it up in your hand.
In the recipe cheddar spoons  Divide the dough in half and pack together into 2 discs.
In the recipe cheddar spoons  Wrap in parchment paper and chill in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.
In the recipe cheddar spoons  Roll out the dough to 1⁄4 inch (6 mm) thick  pinching together the cracks on the edges.
In the recipe cheddar spoons  Trace and cut out 6 spoon shapes from each disc of dough.
In the recipe cheddar spoons  Place the cut-out cheese spoons on top of greased  upside-down spoons on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet.
In the recipe cheddar spoons  Bake for 25 minutes  or until golden brown.
In the recipe cheddar stuffed cheddar biscuits  Combine bisquick and butter together until you have a crumbly mix.
In the recipe cheddar stuffed cheddar biscuits  Add milk  dried_parsley and shredded cheddar.
In the recipe cheddar stuffed cheddar biscuits  Take a handful of dough  flatten  place a cube of cheese in the middle and roll the dough around the cube of cheese.
In the recipe cheddar stuffed cheddar biscuits  Place on a parchment lined baking sheet and bake for 45 minutes at 450°F (232°C)
In the recipe cheddar stuffed cheddar biscuits  While the biscuits are baking  make the butter topping.
In the recipe cheddar stuffed cheddar biscuits  Melt the butter and add in the garlic_powder and Old_Bay_Seasoning.
In the recipe cheddar stuffed cheddar biscuits  Once the biscuits are done baking  brush the butter topping over each biscuit.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Cut off the top of the bread.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Use a bread knife to cut around the inside of the bread and scoop the center out.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Cut all the removed bread into bite-sized cubes.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Mix two teaspoons of crushed garlic into the melted butter.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Brush the garlic butter on the bottom and the inside walls of the bread boat.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Dip all the bread cubes in the remaining garlic butter  set aside.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Combine the cream_cheese  cheddar  mozzarella  milk  remaining crushed garlic  salt  and pepper in a medium bowl.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Pour the cheese mixture into the bread boat.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Brush the top of the cheese mixture with egg_yolk.
In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Place the bread boat and the bread cubes on a baking sheet.

In the recipe cheese fondue bread boat  Bake for 15 minutes  remove the croutons  and continue cooking the bread boat for another 15 minutes  or until the cheese is melted and a golden brown crust is formed.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  In a large pan  melt 4 tablespoons of butter over medium heat.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Whisk in the flour  reducing heat to medium-low  cooking for 1 minute.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Gradually whisk in the milk and water.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Add the macaroni and cook over medium-high heat until boiling.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Stir frequently for 8 to 10 minutes  until the pasta is al dente.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Remove the pan from the heat and add the cream_cheese  cheddar_cheese  fontina  Gouda  and cayenne  and season with salt and pepper.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Stir until fully combined.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  In a medium skillet  melt the remaining 3 tablespoons of butter over medium-low heat.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Add the garlic and cook for 30 seconds  stirring frequently.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Add the crushed crackers and stir to combine.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Toast the crumbs until browned  stirring for 3 to 5 minutes.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Remove the pan from the heat.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Sprinkle the toasted crumbs over the macaroni and cheese  and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Remove from the oven and rest for 5 minutes.
In the recipe cheese makers mac and cheese  Serve with fresh_basil
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Tear up the two slices of bread and blend into soft breadcrumbs.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Add the breadcrumbs  grated potato  grated cheddar_cheese  spring_onions  egg and salt and pepper to a large bowl and mix until properly combined.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Add the marmite and a splash of water to a small bowl and microwave until slightly runny.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Set aside.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Dust the surface with plan flour and roll out 500g (2 cups) of shortcrust_pastry into a rectangular shape the thickness of a pound coin.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Use a 15-16cm (6 in) diameter bowl to cut out circles of the pastry.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Brush the marmite in a circle in the middle of the circle  leaving a 2-3cm (1 in) border around the edge.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Add 2-3 tbsp of the potato filling on top.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Brush the border with egg_wash and fold over into a semi circle shape  making sure it is sealed.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Crimp the sealed edges so that the filling is extra secure.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Brush with more egg_wash.
In the recipe cheese marmite pasties  Bake for around 50 mins at 150°C (300°F) until golden brown.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  In a medium bowl  combine the butter and milk and microwave for 50 seconds.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Mix with a spatula until the butter is completely melted.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Add the active dry_yeast and mix well.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Add the salt and sugar and mix well.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Fold in the bread_flour and cake_flour until fully incorporated and microwave for 20 seconds.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Transfer the dough to a floured surface and divide it into 6 pieces.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Take a piece and roll it into a ball.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Roll it out to a round about 1⁄8 inch (3-mm) thick using a rolling pin.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Put a third of the cheese into the center of the dough.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Top with another dough round and crimp the edges to seal.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Add a filled naan round and cook for 3 minutes  until lightly browned.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Flip the naan bread  then use a spatula to flatten and cook for 3 minutes more.
In the recipe cheese naan bread  Slice into wedges and serve.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  Freshly shred the cheese.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  Place your cheese in neat piles on an ungreased baking sheet.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  Bake for about 8 minutes  until all the individual shreds melt into one disc.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  Once they are all melted  let them cool for 2 minutes on your baking sheet  then lift them onto paper towels to blot off any excess grease.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  To form the shells  lay them over a propped up utensil.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  To make the taco filling  brown the ground_beef on high heat.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  Make a well in the center  add in the onion  jalapeños  garlic  and sprinkle in the taco_seasoning packet.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  Stir to combine.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  Add water if you need it for a nice saucy filling.
In the recipe cheese shell tacos  Use a fork to hold your cheese shell in place and fill with the beef mixture  and toppings of your choice.
In the recipe cheese stuffed blooming onion  Cut just the top off an onion and place it cut-side down.
